Chile Stocks: Cap and Lan Airlines Fall; Empresas La Polar Gains

-- B y   E d u a r d o   T h o m s o n
-- 
2011-07-08T21:13:51Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-08/chilean-stocks-cap-empresas-la-polar-and-lan-airlines.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Chilean trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 4:12 a.m. New York time.  The Ipsa index fell 0.2 percent to 4,769.39.  Cap SA (CAP)   fell 1.1 percent, the most in three weeks,
to 22,948 pesos. Chile’s largest steel producer and iron miner
fell as prices of base metals retreated on a lower-than-forecast
payrolls report in the U.S.  Empresas La Polar SA (LAPOLAR)   rose 2.4 percent to
649.29 pesos, its fourth day of gains. Shareholders at the
Chilean department-store operator under investigation for
consumer loan irregularities and accounting fraud elected a new
board of directors today.  Lan Airlines SA (LAN)   fell 0.7 percent to 14,048 pesos.
 Latin America ’s largest airline by market value has retreated
1.6 percent in the past two days, its biggest two-day fall in
three weeks. Chile’s antitrust court may not rule on the
company’s planned takeover of  Brazil ’s Tam SA until August, La
Tercera reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eduardo Thomson in Santiago at 
 ethomson1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
